    {
      "node_id": "christov_qrs_segmenter",
      "parent_id": "christov_segmenter_root",
      "name": "christov_qrs_segmenter",
      "description": "Detects QRS complex onset and offset positions in an ECG signal using the Christov real-time algorithm, which applies a series of signal transformations and adaptive thresholding to locate heartbeat boundaries.",
      "concept_type": "signal_filter",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "name": "signal",
          "type_desc": "1-D numeric array representing the raw ECG signal",
          "constraints": "must be a non-empty array of finite real values",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "sampling_rate",
          "type_desc": "positive integer or float representing samples per second",
          "constraints": "must be > 0",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "rpeaks",
          "type_desc": "1-D integer array of sample indices corresponding to detected R-peak (QRS) locations",
          "constraints": "indices must be within bounds of the input signal; sorted ascending",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        }
      ],
      "status": "decomposed",
      "children": [
        "initialize_timing_parameters",
        "suppress_powerline_and_emg_noise",
        "bandpass_filter_signal",
        "compute_nonlinear_energy_envelope",
        "initialize_adaptive_threshold_state",
        "run_adaptive_threshold_qrs_detection",
        "refine_rpeaks_on_original_signal"
      ],
      "depth": 1,
      "type_signature": "(signal: 1-D numeric array representing the raw ECG signal, sampling_rate: positive integer or float representing samples per second) -> 1-D integer array of sample indices corresponding to detected R-peak (QRS) locations",
      "matched_primitive": null,
      "primitive_binding_confidence": 0.0,
      "primitive_binding_source": "",
      "is_optional": false,
      "is_opaque": false,
      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "adaptive_impulse_onset_detector. Applies a cascade of nonlinear signal transformations (e.g., differentiation, squaring, moving-window integration) to a uniformly-sampled 1-D scalar time series in order to amplify transient high-energy events relative to baseline activity. An adaptive threshold, which continuously updates based on recent signal statistics, is then swept across the transformed envelope to mark the discrete sample indices where impulse-like events begin and end. The result is a sparse set of integer indices that partition the original time axis into event and non-event regions.. Applications: Seismology \u2014 detecting the precise onset and termination indices of P-wave and S-wave arrivals within a continuously recorded ground-motion time series, where the transient energy bursts of seismic phases must be distinguished from ambient noise using an adaptive baseline that adjusts for varying microseismic activity levels., Industrial condition monitoring \u2014 locating high-energy mechanical impact events (e.g., bearing defect impulses, tool-chatter spikes) within a vibration-sensor data stream sampled at kilohertz rates, enabling real-time fault detection without manual threshold tuning as machine operating conditions drift., Neuroscience / extracellular electrophysiology \u2014 identifying spike-event indices in a raw multi-unit neural recording voltage trace, where action-potential waveforms appear as brief, high-amplitude transients superimposed on a fluctuating local-field-potential background that requires a continuously adapting detection boundary., Acoustic event detection \u2014 segmenting a continuous audio waveform (e.g., bat echolocation calls, gunshot acoustics, sonar pings) into discrete call-onset and call-offset indices by transforming the raw pressure signal into a smoothed energy envelope and applying a time-varying threshold that tracks ambient background loudness.",
      "critic_notes": "",
      "decomposition_rationale": ""
    },
